{Cougaar Plugins}

  These are plugins (in the sense of the cougaar multi agent system) that encapsulate the different
  blexisma functionality for use in cougaar environment. 
  
*----------+-----------------------------------------------------------------+----------------+
  <<plugin>> | <<Description>>                                                     | <<current version>>|
*----------+-----------------------------------------------------------------+----------------+
  {{{/blexisma-cougaar-plugins//blexisma-broker}blexisma-broker}} | A simple broker plugin used to help agents requiring specific service to find them.  | 1.0-SNAPSHOT   |
*----------+-----------------------------------------------------------------+----------------+
  {{{/blexisma-cougaar-plugins//blexisma-sample-ping}blexisma-sample-ping}} | A plugin sample using the "ping" application of cougaar to test/demonstrate the plugin architecture.  | 1.0-SNAPSHOT   |
*----------+-----------------------------------------------------------------+----------------+

{Cougaar Societies}

  Societies are standalone jar + descriptors of a set of agents to be run under the cougaar multi agent system. 
  Such societies are used to run a specific experiment using the cougaar plugins, that may be dispatched on
  several machines.
  
*----------+-----------------------------------------------------------------+----------------+
  <<plugin>> | <<Description>>                                                     | <<current version>>|
*----------+-----------------------------------------------------------------+----------------+
  {{{/blexisma-societies//blexisma-sample-society}blexisma-sample-society}} | A sample society on which other should be built.  | 1.0-SNAPSHOT   |
*----------+-----------------------------------------------------------------+----------------+

